7Ô∏è‚É£ Beware of mishaps or tricks when partnering. Often partners will either forget to include the emojis - in which case you must make sure they post the proper emojis. Another mishap or trick is if they say they will ping everyone - but instead they post the message WITHOUT the ping and then EDIT IN the ping. Let me be clear, editing in @/everyone DOES NOT ping everyone, make sure the message is not edited.

8Ô∏è‚É£ You are required to do a *minimum* of **2** partnerships per week, failure to meet this goal will result in removal from the team, demotion, or some other punishment. 

9Ô∏è‚É£ The first Officer to complete the 2 partnerships will be exempt from doing them the next week, however - if the 1st person to do partnerships does them after Wednesday 11:59PM PST (the half way point of the partnership week), they will not be exempt from next week's partnerships.

üîü Officers who complete *both* partnerships on the last day of the partnership week (Saturday) are given an additional 1 partnership to do the following week. 

1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ Officers are permitted to, instead of doing the normal 2 partnerships per week, invite 4 people (who must stay, i.e not leavers). Officers who invite all 4 people on the last day of the partnership week are assigned 2 extra invites or 1 extra partnership the following week.

1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ Punishments of additional partnerships are effective for only **1** week in a row, i.e if you miss your partnership goal for 2 weeks back-to-back, you will just be removed from the team.
